{"type":"message","id":"c12652e7","parentId":"71fe1203","timestamp":"2026-04-21T05:24:28.473Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"795\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"794\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1154988359\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Final Play id:-5153807254\",\n  \"sender\": \"Dev\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-04-21 05:24 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Final Play\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Dev (1154988359)\",\n  \"id\": \"1154988359\",\n  \"name\": \"Dev\",\n  \"username\": \"Oxpranav\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"emily_bot\",\n  \"body\": \"boss, there isn’t a special “subagent folder” in the codebase.\\n\\nWhat happened is:\\n\\n• subagents run as isolated sessions\\n• they inherit the same workspace root: /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace\\n• unless I explicitly tell them to write files into a named directory, no new folder gets created\\n\\nI checked, and there are no recent subagents currently listed on this session anyway.\\n\\nSo the short answer:\\n\\n• folder for subagent 1: none\\n• folder for subagent 2: none\\n• shared working dir they would have used: /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace\\n\\nIf you want, I can now make this less confusing and set up something like:\\n\\n• subagents/research-1/\\n• subagents/research-2/\\n\\nso every future run leaves obvious artifacts instead of ghost vibes.\"\n}\n```\n\nso basically the subagents that we have they are basically you with a changed name ? right"}],"timestamp":1776749068473}}
