 a question about prior work, and I'm not sure if the user needs tools for their answer. Maybe I can base it on some general knowledge instead. I think I could mention that session architecture documents might not be necessary for this response, but I'm unsure about what specific details to provide. It feels like there's a lot to consider here, but I want to keep it clear and relevant for the user!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] basically: **not just me with a fake mustache**, no 🤭\n\nMore accurate:\n- a subagent is a **separate isolated session**\n- it usually has the **same base capabilities/instructions family**\n- but it runs with its **own context window, its own task, and its own thread of work**\n- I can delegate to it, but it is **not the same live mind/process** as this main chat reply\n\nSo:\n- **same system family / same workspace access pattern** → yes, often\n- **same exact conversation state as me** → no\n- **same identity/persona by default** → not necessarily in a meaningful way\n- **independent worker I can assign a scoped task to** → yes\n\nThink of it like:\n- **me here** = front desk / coordinator\n- **subagent** = a temporary specialist I spin up to go do one job and report back\n\nSo if you’re asking “is it just Emily duplicated with another label?”:\n- **kind of structurally**\n- **not literally conversationally**\n\nThey’re closer to **parallel worker sessions** than “me but renamed.”","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a05b6c3657906520169e70a10bb1081919bce886df2dfa16c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":6277,"output":277,"cacheRead":4608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11162,"cost":{"input":0.0156925,"output":0.004155,"cacheRead":0.001152,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0209995}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776749068473}}
{"type":"message","id":"0dfcfbbe","parentId":"bfbff347","timestamp":"2026-04-21T05:36:11.380Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"797\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"796\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1154988359\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Final Play id:-5153807254\",\n  \"sender\": \"Dev\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-04-21 05:36 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Final Play\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Dev (1154988359)\",\n  \"id\": \"1154988359\",\n  \"name\": \"Dev\",\n  \"username\": \"Oxpranav\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"emily_bot\",\n  \"body\": \"basically: not just me with a fake mustache, no 🤭\\n\\nMore accurate:\\n\\n• a subagent is a separate isolated session\\n• it usually has the same base capabilities/instructions family\\n• but it runs with its own context window, its own task, and its own thread of work\\n• I can delegate to it, but it is not the same live mind/process as this main chat reply\\n\\nSo:\\n\\n• same system family / same workspace access pattern → yes, often\\n• same exact conversation state as me → no\\n• same identity/persona by default → not necessarily in a meaningful way\\n• independent worker I can assign a scoped task to → yes\\n\\nThink of it like:\\n\\n• me here = front desk / coordinator\\n• subagent = a temporary specialist I spin up to go do one job and report back\\n\\nSo if you’re asking “is it just Emily duplicated with another label?”:\\n\\n• kind of structurally\\n• not literally conversationally\\n\\nThey’re closer to parallel worker sessions than “me but renamed.”\"\n}\n```\n\ndescribe me what 2 subagents are doing and how did @Thatiswolf  made you set them up ?"}],"timestamp":1776749771380}}
