{"type":"message","id":"4148fb91","parentId":"79980b43","timestamp":"2026-04-21T05:36:23.095Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_DVjoblTRep01UwjiozaKs174|fc_0a05b6c3657906520169e70cd6a670819192e89dfc19057e3b","toolName":"sessions_history","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:telegram:group:-5153807254\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"i want you to tell me where did you make the folder for both subagents i cannot find it in the codebase\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1776748977572,\n      \"senderLabel\": \"Dev (1154988359)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Determining the approach**\\n\\nI need to figure out if I can answer without using tools, so I'll scan my skills first. None clearly apply, but I might mention that subagents have isolated sessions inheriting the workspace directory, although not necessarily folders. I wonder if I need to inspect those sessions? Since the user asked about prior work, I guess I might need to run a memory search first to gather relevant details. Let's do that!\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_MgvJ0G9tX9dstSQSHdsRSBah|fc_0a05b6c3657906520169e709b6ea508191a0ee0fcbb78293b6\",\n          \"name\": \"memory_search\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"query\": \"subagents folder location where created both subagents folder in codebase research subagents\",\n            \"maxResults\": 5,\n            \"minScore\": 0.2\n          },\n          \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"query\\\":\\\"subagents folder location where created both subagents folder in codebase research subagents\\\", \\\"maxResults\\\": 5, \\\"minScore\\\": 0.2}\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.4\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776748977572\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Checking sessions and subagents**\\n\\nI need to inspect the sessions or subagents to see if they were spawned. I could answer that no folder was created unless one was specifically made. So, I should check the sessions list or the subagents list, maybe through the completion? There’s a lot to consider here, and I want to ensure I'm looking in the right places to get the information I need.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_2vECcfv558IXAcqz69MtlE8Q|fc_0a05b6c3657906520169e709bbb8d08191a934150667097760\",\n          \"name\": \"subagents\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"action\": \"list\",\n            \"recentMinutes\": 120\n          },\n          \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"action\\\":\\\"list\\\",\\\"recentMinutes\\\":120}\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.4\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776748983148\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" boss, there isn’t a special “subagent folder” in the codebase.\\n\\nWhat happened is:\\n- subagents run as isolated sessions\\n- they inherit the same workspace root: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace`\\n- unless I explicitly tell them to write files into a named directory, no new folder gets created\\n\\nI checked, and there are no recent subagents currently listed on this session anyway.\\n\\nSo the short answer:\\n- folder for subagent 1: none\\n- folder for subagent 2: none\\n- shared working dir they would have used: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace`\\n\\nIf you want, I can now make this less confusing and set up something like:\\n- `subagents/research-1/`\\n- `subagents/research-2/`\\n\\nso every future run leaves obvious artifacts instead of ghost vibes.\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0a05b6c3657906520169e709bef51c8191994f52d8df11145d\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.4\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776748987986\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"so basically the subagents that we have they are basically you with a changed name ? right\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1776749068473,\n      \"senderLabel\": \"Dev (1154988359)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating response options**\\n\\nI see there’s a question about prior work, and I'm not sure if the user needs tools for their answer. Maybe I can base it on some general knowledge instead. I think I could mention that session architecture documents might not be necessary for this response, but I'm unsure about what specific details to provide. It feels like there's a lot to consider here, but I want to keep it clear and relevant for the user!\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \" basically: **not just me with a fake mustache**, no 🤭\\n\\nMore accurate:\\n- a subagent is a **separate isolated session**\\n- it usually has the **same base capabilities/instructions family**\\n- but it runs with its **own context window, its own task, and its own thread of work**\\n- I can delegate to it, but it is **not the same live mind/process** as this main chat reply\\n\\nSo:\\n- **same system family / same workspace access pattern** → yes, often\\n- **same exact conversation state as me** → no\\n- **same identity/persona by default** → not necessarily in a meaningful way\\n- **independent worker I can assign a scoped task to** → yes\\n\\nThink of it like:\\n- **me here** = front desk / coordinator\\n- **subagent** = a temporary specialist I spin up to go do one job and report back\\n\\nSo if you’re asking “is it just Emily duplicated with another label?”:\\n- **kind of structurally**\\n- **not literally conversationally**\\n\\nThey’re closer to **parallel worker sessions** than “me but renamed.”\",\n          \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0a05b6c3657906520169e70a10bb1081919bce886df2dfa16c\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.4\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776749068473\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"describe me what 2 subagents are doing and how did @Thatiswolf  made you set them up ?\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1776749771380,\n      \"senderLabel\": \"Dev (1154988359)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_PAt8Bg2r3TIZ6u6FwpVWM7jj|fc_0a05b6c3657906520169e70cce82b48191b25eed5b2de79b7a\",\n          \"name\": \"memory_search\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"query\": \"Thatiswolf set up two subagents what were they doing how did he make you set them up\",\n            \"maxResults\": 10,\n            \"minScore\": 0.2\n          },\n          \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"query\\\":\\\"Thatiswolf set up two subagents what were they doing how did he make you set them up\\\", \\\"maxResults\\\": 10, \\\"minScore\\\": 0.2}\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.4\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776749771380\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_dpT33dj5vIxxeeTt3jidQ89y|fc_0a05b6c3657906520169e70cd217e08191905a63a15d3ef482\",\n          \"name\": \"sessions_list\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"kinds\": [\n              \"chat\"\n            ],\n            \"limit\": 10,\n            \"activeMinutes\": 180,\n            \"messageLimit\": 2\n          },\n          \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"kinds\\\":[\\\"chat\\\"],\\\"limit\\\":10,\\\"activeMinutes\\\":180,\\\"messageLimit\\\":2}\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.4\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1776749775179\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_DVjoblTRep01UwjiozaKs174|fc_0a05b6c3657906520169e70cd6a670819192e89dfc19057e3b\",\n          \"name\": \"sessions_history\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:telegram:group:-5153807254\",\n            \"limit\": 30,\n            \"includeTools\": false\n          },\n          \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"sessionKey\\\":\\\"agent:main:telegram:group:-5153807254\\\",\\\"limit\\\":30,\\\"includeTools\\\":false}\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n      \"model\":