{"type":"message","id":"a8a72b9b","parentId":"9a990373","timestamp":"2026-04-21T05:45:39.178Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_xkeb5LkEhsUsGSpYXt1bXfsS|fc_0a05b6c3657906520169e70f01f2cc81919b863a4d2c6aff59","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/experiments/plans/acp-thread-bound-agents.md:661:- route thread-bound ACP turns from dispatch pipeline into ACP manager\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/experiments/plans/acp-thread-bound-agents.md:690:- add full telemetry, dashboards, and alert thresholds\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/experiments/plans/acp-thread-bound-agents.md:724:- thread-bound inbound routing to ACP session key\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/experiments/plans/acp-thread-bound-agents.md:725:- thread-bound outbound delivery suppresses parent channel duplication\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/experiments/plans/acp-persistent-bindings-discord-channels-telegram-topics.md:18:Current thread-bound ACP behavior is optimized for ephemeral Discord thread workflows. Telegram does not have the same thread model; it has forum topics in groups/supergroups. Users want stable, always-on ACP “workspaces” in chat surfaces, not only temporary thread sessions.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/ja-JP/start/wizard.md:26:最速で初回チャットを開始する方法：Control UI を開きます（チャンネル設定は不要）。`openclaw dashboard` を実行してブラウザでチャットできます。ドキュメント：[Dashboard](/web/dashboard)。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/ja-JP/start/getting-started.md:21:最速のチャット方法：Control UIを開く（チャンネル設定は不要）。`openclaw dashboard`を実行してブラウザでチャットするか、<Tooltip headline=\"Gatewayホスト\" tip=\"OpenClaw Gatewayサービスを実行しているマシン。\">Gatewayホスト</Tooltip>で`http://127.0.0.1:18789/`を開きます。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/ja-JP/start/getting-started.md:22:ドキュメント：[Dashboard](/web/dashboard)と[Control UI](/web/control-ui)。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/ja-JP/start/getting-started.md:74:    openclaw dashboard\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/ja-JP/index.md:46:  <Card title=\"Control UIを開く\" href=\"/web/control-ui\" icon=\"layout-dashboard\">\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/perplexity.md:20:2. Generate an API key in the dashboard\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/web/dashboard.md:11:  source_path: web/dashboard.md\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/web/dashboard.md:40:- 随时重新打开：`openclaw dashboard`（复制链接，如果可能则打开浏览器，如果是无头环境则显示 SSH 提示）。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/web/dashboard.md:45:- **Localhost**：打开 `http://127.0.0.1:18789/`。如果你看到\"unauthorized\"，运行 `openclaw dashboard` 并使用带 token 的链接（`?token=...`）。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/web/dashboard.md:51:- 运行 `openclaw dashboard` 获取新的带 token 链接。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/help/faq.md:22:  - [新手引导后如何打开仪表板？](#how-do-i-open-the-dashboard-after-onboarding)\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/help/faq.md:23:  - [如何在本地和远程环境中验证仪表板（令牌）？](#how-do-i-authenticate-the-dashboard-token-on-localhost-vs-remote)\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/help/faq.md:344:- 如果要求认证，运行 `openclaw dashboard` 并使用带令牌的链接（`?token=...`）。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/help/faq.md:351:- **SSH 隧道**：`ssh -N -L 18789:127.0.0.1:18789 user@host`，然后从 `openclaw dashboard` 打开 `http://127.0.0.1:18789/?token=...`。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/help/faq.md:353:参阅[仪表板](/web/dashboard)和 [Web 界面](/web)了解绑定模式和认证详情。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/help/faq.md:2213:- 最快：`openclaw dashboard`（打印 + 复制带令牌的链接，尝试打开；如果无头则显示 SSH 提示）。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/help/faq.md:2218:- 仍然卡住？运行 `openclaw status --all` 并按[故障排除](/gateway/troubleshooting)操作。参阅[仪表板](/web/dashboard)了解认证详情。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/help/faq.md:2376:3. UI 有正确的令牌吗？`openclaw dashboard`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/help/faq.md:2385:文档：[仪表板](/web/dashboard)、[远程访问](/gateway/remote)、[故障排除](/gateway/troubleshooting)。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/tools/multi-agent-sandbox-tools.md:237:- `group:sessions`：`sessions_list`、`sessions_history`、`sessions_send`、`sessions_spawn`、`session_status`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/tools/subagents.md:4:  - 你正在更改 sessions_spawn 或子智能体工具策略\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/tools/subagents.md:54:使用 `sessions_spawn`：\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/tools/subagents.md:58:- 默认模型：继承调用者，除非你设置了 `agents.defaults.subagents.model`（或每智能体的 `agents.list[].subagents.model`）；显式的 `sessions_spawn.model` 仍然优先。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/tools/subagents.md:59:- 默认思考：继承调用者，除非你设置了 `agents.defaults.subagents.thinking`（或每智能体的 `agents.list[].subagents.thinking`）；显式的 `sessions_spawn.thinking` 仍然优先。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/tools/subagents.md:77:- 使用 `agents_list` 查看当前允许用于 `sessions_spawn` 的智能体 id。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/tools/subagents.md:125:- `sessions_spawn`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/tools/subagents.md:166:- `sessions_spawn` 始终是非阻塞的：它立即返回 `{ status: \"accepted\", runId, childSessionKey }`。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/tools/index.md:154:- `group:sessions`：`sessions_list`、`sessions_history`、`sessions_send`、`sessions_spawn`、`session_status`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/tools/index.md:434:### `sessions_list` / `sessions_history` / `sessions_send` / `sessions_spawn` / `session_status`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/tools/index.md:443:- `sessions_spawn`：`task`、`label?`、`agentId?`、`model?`、`runTimeoutSeconds?`、`cleanup?`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/tools/index.md:452:- `sessions_spawn` 启动子智能体运行并将宣告回复发送回请求者聊天。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/tools/index.md:453:- `sessions_spawn` 是非阻塞的，立即返回 `status: \"accepted\"`。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/tools/index.md:459:列出当前会话可以用 `sessions_spawn` 定位的智能体 id。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/cli/dashboard.md:5:summary: \"`openclaw dashboard` 的 CLI 参考（打开控制界面）\"\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/cli/dashboard.md:6:title: dashboard\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/cli/dashboard.md:12:  source_path: cli/dashboard.md\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/cli/dashboard.md:16:# `openclaw dashboard`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/cli/dashboard.md:21:openclaw dashboard\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/cli/dashboard.md:22:openclaw dashboard --no-open\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/cli/onboard.md:36:- 最快开始聊天：`openclaw dashboard`（控制 UI，无需渠道设置）。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/cli/index.md:27:- [`dashboard`](/cli/dashboard)\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/gateway/security/index.md:654:            \"sessions_spawn\",\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/gateway/sandbox-vs-tool-policy-vs-elevated.md:97:- `group:sessions`：`sessions_list`、`sessions_history`、`sessions_send`、`sessions_spawn`、`session_status`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/gateway/configuration.md:761:    - `allowAgents`：允许从此智能体执行 `sessions_spawn` 的智能体 id 白名单（`[\"*\"]` = 允许任何；默认：仅同一智能体）\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/gateway/configuration.md:830:            \"sessions_spawn\",\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/gateway/configuration.md:860:            \"sessions_spawn\",\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/gateway/configuration.md:2164:- `group:sessions`：`sessions_list`、`sessions_history`、`sessions_send`、`sessions_spawn`、`session_status`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/gateway/configuration.md:2241:- 工具策略：仅允许 `exec`、`process`、`read`、`write`、`edit`、`apply_patch`、`sessions_list`、`sessions_history`、`sessions_send`、`sessions_spawn`、`session_status`（deny 优先）\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/gateway/configuration.md:2325:          \"sessions_spawn\",\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/concepts/session-tool.md:24:- `sessions_spawn`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/concepts/session-tool.md:150:## sessions_spawn\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/concepts/session-tool.md:169:- 使用 `agents_list` 发现哪些智能体 id 允许用于 `sessions_spawn`。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/concepts/session-tool.md:175:- 子智能体不允许调用 `sessions_spawn`（无子智能体 → 子智能体生成）。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/concepts/session-tool.md:185:沙箱隔离的会话可以使用会话工具，但默认情况下它们只能看到通过 `sessions_spawn` 生成的会话。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/concepts/multi-agent.md:297:            \"sessions_spawn\",\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/prose.md:131:| 生成会话 / Task 工具 | `sessions_spawn` |\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/start/wizard.md:27:最快开始聊天的方式：打开控制界面（无需设置渠道）。运行 `openclaw dashboard` 并在浏览器中聊天。文档：[控制面板](/web/dashboard)。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/start/getting-started.md:20:最快聊天：打开 Control UI（无需渠道设置）。运行 `openclaw dashboard` 并在浏览器中聊天，或在 Gateway 网关主机上打开 `http://127.0.0.1:18789/`。文档：[Dashboard](/web/dashboard) 和 [Control UI](/web/control-ui)。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/start/openclaw.md:101:新手引导完成后，我们会自动打开带有 Gateway 网关令牌的仪表板并打印带令牌的链接。稍后重新打开：`openclaw dashboard`。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/start/showcase.md:382:  <img src=\"/assets/showcase/gohome-grafana.png\" alt=\"GoHome Grafana dashboard\" />\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/start/hubs.md:102:- [仪表盘](/web/dashboard)\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/install/docker.md:66:- 需要再次获取带令牌的 URL？运行 `docker compose run --rm openclaw-cli dashboard --no-open`。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/install/docker.md:94:docker compose run --rm openclaw-cli dashboard --no-open\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/install/docker.md:99:更多详情：[仪表板](/web/dashboard)，[设备](/cli/devices)。\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/install/docker.md:328:- 默认允许：`exec`、`process`、`read`、`write`、`edit`、`sessions_list`、`sessions_history`、`sessions_send`、`sessions_spawn`、`session_status`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/install/docker.md:391:          \"sessions_spawn\",\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/install/exe-dev.md:40:Set up OpenClaw (https://docs.openclaw.ai/install) on this VM. Use the non-interactive and accept-risk flags for openclaw onboarding. Add the supplied auth or token as needed. Configure nginx to forward from the default port 18789 to the root location on the default enabled site config, making sure to enable Websocket support. Pairing is done by \"openclaw devices list\" and \"openclaw device approve <request id>\". Make sure the dashboard shows that OpenClaw's health is OK. exe.dev handles forwarding from port 8000 to port 80/443 and HTTPS for us, so the final \"reachable\" should be <vm-name>.exe.xyz, without port specification.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/install/index.md:125:- 打开仪表板：`openclaw dashboard`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/index.md:46:  <Card title=\"打开控制界面\" href=\"/web/control-ui\" icon=\"layout-dashboard\">\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/discord.md:681:    - `spawnSubagentSessions` must be true to auto-create/bind threads for `sessions_spawn({ thread: true })`.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/discord.md:682:    - `spawnAcpSessions` must be true to auto-create/bind threads for ACP (`/acp spawn ... --thread ...` or `sessions_spawn({ runtime: \"acp\", thread: true })`).\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/googlechat.md:66:Google Chat webhooks require a public HTTPS endpoint. For security, **only expose the `/googlechat` path** to the internet. Keep the OpenClaw dashboard and other sensitive endpoints on your private network.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/googlechat.md:70:Use Tailscale Serve for the private dashboard and Funnel for the public webhook path. This keeps `/` private while exposing only `/googlechat`.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/googlechat.md:80:2. **Expose the dashboard to the tailnet only (port 8443):**\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/googlechat.md:113:Your private dashboard stays tailnet-only:\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/dashboard.md:2:summary: \"Gateway dashboard (Control UI) access and auth\"\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/dashboard.md:4:  - Changing dashboard authentication or exposure modes\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/dashboard.md:10:The Gateway dashboard is the browser Control UI served at `/` by default\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/dashboard.md:27:Do not expose it publicly. The UI keeps dashboard URL tokens in sessionStorage\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/dashboard.md:33:- After onboarding, the CLI auto-opens the dashboard and prints a clean (non-tokenized) link.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/dashboard.md:34:- Re-open anytime: `openclaw dashboard` (copies link, opens browser if possible, shows SSH hint if headless).\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/dashboard.md:40:- **Token source**: `gateway.auth.token` (or `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN`); `openclaw dashboard` can pass it via URL fragment for one-time bootstrap, and the Control UI keeps it in sessionStorage for the current browser tab session and selected gateway URL instead of localStorage.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/dashboard.md:41:- If `gateway.auth.token` is SecretRef-managed, `openclaw dashboard` prints/copies/opens a non-tokenized URL by design. This avoids exposing externally managed tokens in shell logs, clipboard history, or browser-launch arguments.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/dashboard.md:42:- If `gateway.auth.token` is configured as a SecretRef and is unresolved in your current shell, `openclaw dashboard` still prints a non-tokenized URL plus actionable auth setup guidance.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/dashboard.md:52:  - SecretRef-managed config: resolve the external secret provider or export `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN` in this shell, then rerun `openclaw dashboard`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/dashboard.md:54:- In the dashboard settings, paste the token into the auth field, then connect.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/control-ui.md:30:  The dashboard settings panel keeps a token for the current browser tab session and selected gateway URL; passwords are not persisted.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/control-ui.md:156:If you open the dashboard over plain HTTP (`http://<lan-ip>` or `http://<tailscale-ip>`),\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/wizard.md:79:      - Quickstart reuses existing `gateway.auth.token` SecretRefs across `env`, `file`, and `exec` providers for onboarding probe/dashboard bootstrap.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/session-management-compaction.md:189:2. **Session store counters**: rolling stats written into `sessions.json` (used for /status and dashboards)\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/api-usage-costs.md:90:1,000 requests/month at no charge. Set your usage limit in the Brave dashboard\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:18:  - [How do I open the dashboard after onboarding?](#how-do-i-open-the-dashboard-after-onboarding)\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:19:  - [How do I authenticate the dashboard (token) on localhost vs remote?](#how-do-i-authenticate-the-dashboard-token-on-localhost-vs-remote)\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:342:### How do I open the dashboard after onboarding\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:344:The wizard opens your browser with a clean (non-tokenized) dashboard URL right after onboarding and also prints the link in the summary. Keep that tab open; if it didn't launch, copy/paste the printed URL on the same machine.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:346:### How do I authenticate the dashboard token on localhost vs remote\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:357:- **Tailnet bind**: run `openclaw gateway --bind tailnet --token \"<token>\"`, open `http://<tailscale-ip>:18789/`, paste token in dashboard settings.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:360:See [Dashboard](/web/dashboard) and [Web surfaces](/web) for bind modes and auth details.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1089:### How do thread-bound subagent sessions work on Discord\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:1095:- Spawn with `sessions_spawn` using `thread: true` (and optionally `mode: \"session\"` for persistent follow-up).\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:2533:- Fastest: `openclaw dashboard` (prints + copies the dashboard URL, tries to open; shows SSH hint if headless).\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:2541:- Still stuck? Run `openclaw status --all` and follow [Troubleshooting](/gateway/troubleshooting). See [Dashboard](/web/dashboard) for auth details.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:2702:3. Does the UI have the right token? `openclaw dashboard`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:2711:Docs: [Dashboard](/web/dashboard), [Remote access](/gateway/remote), [Troubleshooting](/gateway/troubleshooting).\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/troubleshooting.md:145:    - [/gateway/troubleshooting#dashboard-control-ui-connectivity](/gateway/troubleshooting#dashboard-control-ui-connectivity)\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/browser.md:260:  from the [Overview dashboard](https://www.browserbase.com/overview).\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md:5:  - Setting up thread-bound ACP sessions on thread-capable channels\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md:61:| Spawn tool    | `sessions_spawn` with `runtime:\"acp\"` | `sessions_spawn` (default runtime) |\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md:76:Required feature flags for thread-bound ACP:\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md:214:### From `sessions_spawn`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md:288:4. Ask that agent to call `sessions_spawn` with:\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md:302:Use the sessions_spawn tool now with runtime: \"acp\", agentId: \"codex\", and mode: \"run\".\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md:310:  thread-bound persistent ACP sessions.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md:313:- Treat thread-bound `mode: \"session\"` testing as a second, richer integration\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md:322:- If the requester session is sandboxed, ACP spawns are blocked for both `sessions_spawn({ runtime: \"acp\" })` and `/acp spawn`.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md:323:  - Error: `Sandboxed sessions cannot spawn ACP sessions because runtime=\"acp\" runs on the host. Use runtime=\"subagent\" from sandboxed sessions.`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md:324:- `sessions_spawn` with `runtime: \"acp\"` does not support `sandbox: \"require\"`.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md:325:  - Error: `sessions_spawn sandbox=\"require\" is unsupported for runtime=\"acp\" because ACP sessions run outside the sandbox. Use runtime=\"subagent\" or sandbox=\"inherit\".`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md:502:If thread-bound ACP spawn does not work, verify the adapter feature flag first:\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/acp-agents.md:619:| `sessions_spawn sandbox=\"require\" is unsupported for runtime=\"acp\" ...`  | `sandbox=\"require\"` requested for ACP runtime.                                  | Use `runtime=\"subagent\"` for required sandboxing, or use ACP with `sandbox=\"inherit\"` from a non-sandboxed session.                                               |\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/multi-agent-sandbox-tools.md:231:- `group:sessions`: `sessions_list`, `sessions_history`, `sessions_send`, `sessions_spawn`, `session_status`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:5:  - You are changing sessions_spawn or sub-agent tool policy\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:6:  - You are implementing or troubleshooting thread-bound subagent sessions\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:55:- `/subagents spawn` is one-shot mode (`mode: \"run\"`). For persistent thread-bound sessions, use `sessions_spawn` with `thread: true` and `mode: \"session\"`.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:56:- For ACP harness sessions (Codex, Claude Code, Gemini CLI), use `sessions_spawn` with `runtime: \"acp\"` and see [ACP Agents](/tools/acp-agents).\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:71:Use `sessions_spawn`:\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:75:- Default model: inherits the caller unless you set `agents.defaults.subagents.model` (or per-agent `agents.list[].subagents.model`); an explicit `sessions_spawn.model` still wins.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:76:- Default thinking: inherits the caller unless you set `agents.defaults.subagents.thinking` (or per-agent `agents.list[].subagents.thinking`); an explicit `sessions_spawn.thinking` still wins.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:77:- Default run timeout: if `sessions_spawn.runTimeoutSeconds` is omitted, OpenClaw uses `agents.defaults.subagents.runTimeoutSeconds` when set; otherwise it falls back to `0` (no timeout).\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:94:- `sessions_spawn` does **not** accept channel-delivery params (`target`, `channel`, `to`, `threadId`, `replyTo`, `transport`). For delivery, use `message`/`sessions_send` from the spawned run.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:102:- Discord (currently the only supported channel): supports persistent thread-bound subagent sessions (`sessions_spawn` with `thread: true`), manual thread controls (`/focus`, `/unfocus`, `/agents`, `/session idle`, `/session max-age`), and adapter keys `channels.discord.threadBindings.enabled`, `channels.discord.threadBindings.idleHours`, `channels.discord.threadBindings.maxAgeHours`, and `channels.discord.threadBindings.spawnSubagentSessions`.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:106:1. Spawn with `sessions_spawn` using `thread: true` (and optionally `mode: \"session\"`).\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:129:- Sandbox inheritance guard: if the requester session is sandboxed, `sessions_spawn` rejects targets that would run unsandboxed.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:133:- Use `agents_list` to see which agent ids are currently allowed for `sessions_spawn`.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:158:        runTimeoutSeconds: 900, // default timeout for sessions_spawn when omitted (0 = no timeout)\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:186:- **Depth 1 (orchestrator, when `maxSpawnDepth >= 2`)**: Gets `sessions_spawn`, `subagents`, `sessions_list`, `sessions_history` so it can manage its children. Other session/system tools remain denied.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:188:- **Depth 2 (leaf worker)**: No session tools — `sessions_spawn` is always denied at depth 2. Cannot spawn further children.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:248:- `sessions_spawn`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:250:When `maxSpawnDepth >= 2`, depth-1 orchestrator sub-agents additionally receive `sessions_spawn`, `subagents`, `sessions_list`, and `sessions_history` so they can manage their children.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:292:- `sessions_spawn` is always non-blocking: it returns `{ status: \"accepted\", runId, childSessionKey }` immediately.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/slash-commands.md:85:- `/agents` (list thread-bound agents for this session)\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/web.md:65:2. In the dashboard, choose the **Search** plan and generate an API key.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/web.md:70:your usage limit in the Brave dashboard to avoid unexpected charges. See the\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/web.md:77:2. Generate an API key in the dashboard\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/index.md:147:- `group:sessions`: `sessions_list`, `sessions_history`, `sessions_send`, `sessions_spawn`, `session_status`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/index.md:474:### `sessions_list` / `sessions_history` / `sessions_send` / `sessions_spawn` / `session_status`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/index.md:483:- `sessions_spawn`: `task`, `label?`, `runtime?`, `agentId?`, `model?`, `thinking?`, `cwd?`, `runTimeoutSeconds?`, `thread?`, `mode?`, `cleanup?`, `sandbox?`, `streamTo?`, `attachments?`, `attachAs?`\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/index.md:493:- `sessions_spawn` supports `runtime: \"subagent\" | \"acp\"` (`subagent` default). For ACP runtime behavior, see [ACP Agents](/tools/acp-agents).\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/index.md:495:- `sessions_spawn` starts a sub-agent run and posts an announce reply back to the requester chat.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/index.md:496:  - Supports one-shot mode (`mode: \"run\"`) and persistent thread-bound mode (`mode: \"session\"` with `thread: true`).\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/index.md:500:  - Discord thread-bound flows depend on `session.threadBindings.*` and `channels.discord.threadBindings.*`.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/index.md:504:- `sessions_spawn` supports inline file attachments for subagent runtime only (ACP rejects them). Each attachment has `name`, `content`, and optional `encoding` (`utf8` or `base64`) and `mimeType`. Files are materialized into the child workspace at `.openclaw/attachments/<uuid>/` with a `.manifest.json` metadata file. The tool returns a receipt with `count`, `totalBytes`, per file `sha256`, and `relDir`. Attachment content is automatically redacted from transcript persistence.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/index.md:505:  - Configure limits via `tools.sessions_spawn.attachments` (`enabled`, `maxTotalBytes`, `maxFiles`, `maxFileBytes`, `retainOnSessionKeep`).\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/index.md:507:- `sessions_spawn` is non-blocking and returns `status: \"accepted\"` immediately.\n/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v25.8.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/index.md:515:List agent ids that the current session may target with `sessions_spawn`.\