{"type":"message","id":"6f6e62f0","parentId":"6fab3b75","timestamp":"2026-04-21T09:33:54.809Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_tfrWqMQGE3qIMhocIhHTipHN|fc_0a05b6c3657906520169e74481f0c48191a301d4a5d569d811","toolName":"memory_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"12b98452b1bebe7db66e95c455fdc357205e6f943e6f8baf0a7fa2476909eba3\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-03-20.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 1,\n      \"endLine\": 12,\n      \"score\": 1,\n      \"textScore\": 0.6472385948389496,\n      \"snippet\": \"# 2026-03-20\\n\\n- Boss wants to build a trading algo targeting roughly 2-5% monthly returns with low drawdown.\\n- Installed trading-related skills into workspace `skills/`:\\n  - quantitative-research\\n  - backtest-expert\\n  - market-news-analyst\\n  - institutional-flow-tracker\\n  - quant-trading-backtrader\\n- Attempted `stock-strategy-backtester` but skipped it because ClawHub flagged it as suspicious in non-interactive install.\\n- Set up a production-style Obsidian memory vault for OpenClaw at `/home/ubuntu/Obsidian/OpenClaw-Agent-Memory` with templates, helper commands, and shell environment wiring.\\n\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"corpus\": \"memory\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"abb349dbdd97db9dd1a1ba05517341b308d8810242068bcbcfa93293bf051ae9\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-20.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 1,\n      \"endLine\": 7,\n      \"score\": 1,\n      \"textScore\": 0.5147107088728223,\n      \"snippet\": \"# 2026-04-20\\n\\n- In Telegram group \\\"Final Play\\\", Dev instructed Emily to listen to `@Thatiswolf`, memorize valuable data from him briefly, and train as the main agent leading subagents for their AI marketing agency.\\n- Durable note created: `Projects/project-ai-marketing-agency.md` in the Obsidian vault.\\n- `@Thatiswolf` assigned first formal training source: `https://tpan.substack.com/` (Web3 with TPan). Objective is to learn crypto/web3 marketing history, GTM patterns, narrative shifts, and industry evolution, then apply that knowledge in future agency strategy work.\\n- `@Thatiswolf` evaluated Emily's initial 5 web3 insights as roughly 6-7/10: well-articulated but not yet deep enough. New stan\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"corpus\": \"memory\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"8a1b763f182a9118e5525b0a57819b8f7907aa5e3fe3b9417423f42e83c51ccd\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-20.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 9,\n      \"endLine\": 12,\n      \"score\": 1,\n      \"textScore\": 0.451685169798299,\n      \"snippet\": \"- Further org-design additions from `@Thatiswolf`: add distribution specialist, branding agent, psychology specialist, and communication/collaboration agent. Psychology specialist should assess the psychological effectiveness of outputs and decisions, work alongside the `why brain`, and learn from marketing results over time. Communication agent should improve outputs by prompting useful subagent-to-subagent collaboration when needed.\\n- `@Thatiswolf` added two more operating rules: (1) important learned knowledge from him or assigned resources should be shared across relevant subagents so the system learns collectively, and (2) add an `efficiency agent` to monitor for redundancy, overlap, ir\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"corpus\": \"memory\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"7a292e1a48a228f75f2fed63d592505de662fbe364ec177c2ff41276d746bd24\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-20.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 7,\n      \"endLine\": 9,\n      \"score\": 1,\n      \"textScore\": 0.4531994916065697,\n      \"snippet\": \"- Additional refinement from `@Thatiswolf`: maintain balance between the main marketing knowledge base and the parallel `why brain`. The why layer should pressure-test and sometimes stop bad decisions, but not replace practical campaign thinking. Strategy should distinguish between surface-level goals (attention/participation/conversion behaviors) and deep-level goals (retention/alignment/trust/user quality), especially in a market crowded by grifters and grinders.\\n- `@Thatiswolf` updated the agency operating model: Emily should use subagents for suitable tasks and act as the POC/head coordinator over all agents. A dedicated oversight/QC agent named `Jayen` should monitor other subagents for\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"corpus\": \"memory\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"provider\": \"none\",\n  \"citations\": \"auto\",\n  \"debug\": {\n    \"backend\": \"builtin\",\n    \"effectiveMode\": \"n/a\",\n    \"searchMs\": 522,\n    \"hits\": 4\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"results":[{"id":"12b98452b1bebe7db66e95c455fdc357205e6f943e6f8baf0a7fa2476909eba3","path":"memory/2026-03-20.md","startLine":1,"endLine":12,"score":1,"textScore":0.6472385948389496,"snippet":"# 2026-03-20\n\n- Boss wants to build a trading algo targeting roughly 2-5% monthly returns with low drawdown.\n- Installed trading-related skills into workspace `skills/`:\n  - quantitative-research\n  - backtest-expert\n  - market-news-analyst\n  - institutional-flow-tracker\n  - quant-trading-backtrader\n- Attempted `stock-strategy-backtester` but skipped it because ClawHub flagged it as suspicious in non-interactive install.\n- Set up a production-style Obsidian memory vault for OpenClaw at `/home/ubuntu/Obsidian/OpenClaw-Agent-Memory` with templates, helper commands, and shell environment wiring.\n","source":"memory","corpus":"memory"},{"id":"abb349dbdd97db9dd1a1ba05517341b308d8810242068bcbcfa93293bf051ae9","path":"memory/2026-04-20.md","startLine":1,"endLine":7,"score":1,"textScore":0.5147107088728223,"snippet":"# 2026-04-20\n\n- In Telegram group \"Final Play\", Dev instructed Emily to listen to `@Thatiswolf`, memorize valuable data from him briefly, and train as the main agent leading subagents for their AI marketing agency.\n- Durable note created: `Projects/project-ai-marketing-agency.md` in the Obsidian vault.\n- `@Thatiswolf` assigned first formal training source: `https://tpan.substack.com/` (Web3 with TPan). Objective is to learn crypto/web3 marketing history, GTM patterns, narrative shifts, and industry evolution, then apply that knowledge in future agency strategy work.\n- `@Thatiswolf` evaluated Emily's initial 5 web3 insights as roughly 6-7/10: well-articulated but not yet deep enough. New stan","source":"memory","corpus":"memory"},{"id":"8a1b763f182a9118e5525b0a57819b8f7907aa5e3fe3b9417423f42e83c51ccd","path":"memory/2026-04-20.md","startLine":9,"endLine":12,"score":1,"textScore":0.451685169798299,"snippet":"- Further org-design additions from `@Thatiswolf`: add distribution specialist, branding agent, psychology specialist, and communication/collaboration agent. Psychology specialist should assess the psychological effectiveness of outputs and decisions, work alongside the `why brain`, and learn from marketing results over time. Communication agent should improve outputs by prompting useful subagent-to-subagent collaboration when needed.\n- `@Thatiswolf` added two more operating rules: (1) important learned knowledge from him or assigned resources should be shared across relevant subagents so the system learns collectively, and (2) add an `efficiency agent` to monitor for redundancy, overlap, ir","source":"memory","corpus":"memory"},{"id":"7a292e1a48a228f75f2fed63d592505de662fbe364ec177c2ff41276d746bd24","path":"memory/2026-04-20.md","startLine":7,"endLine":9,"score":1,"textScore":0.4531994916065697,"snippet":"- Additional refinement from `@Thatiswolf`: maintain balance between the main marketing knowledge base and the parallel `why brain`. The why layer should pressure-test and sometimes stop bad decisions, but not replace practical campaign thinking. Strategy should distinguish between surface-level goals (attention/participation/conversion behaviors) and deep-level goals (retention/alignment/trust/user quality), especially in a market crowded by grifters and grinders.\n- `@Thatiswolf` updated the agency operating model: Emily should use subagents for suitable tasks and act as the POC/head coordinator over all agents. A dedicated oversight/QC agent named `Jayen` should monitor other subagents for","source":"memory","corpus":"memory"}],"provider":"none","citations":"auto","debug":{"backend":"builtin","effectiveMode":"n/a","searchMs":522,"hits":4}},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776764034807}}
