al possibilities** here:\\n1. they were never really spawned and I described intended delegation,\\n2. they were spawned as temporary sessions and left no code folder,\\n3. they were ACP/subagent sessions outside the repo structure, so you wouldn’t “find them in codebase” at all.\\n\\nRight now, based on evidence, **#2 or #1 looks more likely than “hidden folder in codebase.”**\",\"textSignature\":\"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0a05b6c3657906520169e70cdb09f0819189c2fc674bddf9f4\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}],\"api\":\"openai-codex-responses\",\"provider\":\"openai-codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4\",\"usage\":{\"input\":2686,\"output\":533,\"cacheRead\":12288,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":15507,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.0067150000000000005,\"output\":0.007995,\"cacheRead\":0.003072,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0.017782}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1776749783095}}\n21:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"f4c25df2\",\"parentId\":\"0e98d48a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-21T05:42:07.518Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"message_id\\\": \\\"799\\\",\\n  \\\"reply_to_id\\\": \\\"798\\\",\\n  \\\"sender_id\\\": \\\"1154988359\\\",\\n  \\\"conversation_label\\\": \\\"Final Play id:-5153807254\\\",\\n  \\\"sender\\\": \\\"Dev\\\",\\n  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"Tue 2026-04-21 05:42 UTC\\\",\\n  \\\"group_subject\\\": \\\"Final Play\\\",\\n  \\\"is_group_chat\\\": true,\\n  \\\"was_mentioned\\\": true,\\n  \\\"has_reply_context\\\": true\\n}\\n```\\n\\nSender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"Dev (1154988359)\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"1154988359\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"Dev\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"Oxpranav\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"sender_label\\\": \\\"emily_bot\\\",\\n  \\\"body\\\": \\\"from what I can verify right now, the two subagents were supposed to do this:\\\\n\\\\n• Subagent 1: look through the TPan feed, find article links that were actually accessible/readable\\\\n• Subagent 2: do the same in parallel, so we could cover more ground faster\\\\n• then, once each had a usable article, they were supposed to process the first 1–2 accessible articles they could actually read\\\\n• goal: come back with which article(s), what was learned, and what mattered\\\\n\\\\nSo the practical split was basically:\\\\n\\\\n• agent A = scout + summarize\\\\n• agent B = second scout + summarize\\\\n• same mission, parallel lanes\\\\n\\\\nAnd on the “how did @Thatiswolf make you set them up?” part:\\\\n\\\\n• I don’t currently have a verifiable record showing some special codebase setup or custom folder-based install by @Thatiswolf\\\\n• I checked what I could, and I don’t see active/recent subagent records in this session now\\\\n• so my best honest answer is: if that happened, it was most likely through chat instructions / task delegation, not by creating a visible “subagent module” somewhere in your repo\\\\n\\\\nSo:\\\\n\\\\n• what they were doing: parallel article-finding + reading on the TPan feed\\\\n• how they were set up: most likely I was told to spawn/delegate two worker sessions, not that someone created two permanent code agents in the repo\\\\n\\\\nIf you want, boss, I can be stricter and tell you the three actual possibilities here:\\\\n\\\\n1. they were never really spawned and I described intended delegation,\\\\n2. they were spawned as temporary sessions and left no code folder,\\\\n3. they were ACP/subagent sessions outside the repo structure, so you wouldn’t “find them in codebase” at all.\\\\n\\\\nRight now, based on evidence, #2 or #1 looks more likely than “hidden folder in codebase.”\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nnow go and create 2 subgents the same way @wolf asked you and make sure they are visible in status and dashboard\"}],\"timestamp\":1776750127517}}\n22:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"5dfd0539\",\"parentId\":\"f4c25df2\",\"timestam