ifiable record** showing some special codebase setup or custom folder-based install by @Thatiswolf\\n- I checked what I could, and I **don’t see active/recent subagent records** in this session now\\n- so my best honest answer is: if that happened, it was most likely **through chat instructions / task delegation**, not by creating a visible “subagent module” somewhere in your repo\\n\\nSo:\\n- **what they were doing:** parallel article-finding + reading on the TPan feed\\n- **how they were set up:** most likely I was **told to spawn/delegate two worker sessions**, not that someone created two permanent code agents in the repo\\n\\nIf you want, boss, I can be stricter and tell you the **three actual possibilities** here:\\n1. they were never really spawned and I described intended delegation,\\n2. they were spawned as temporary sessions and left no code folder,\\n3. they were ACP/subagent sessions outside the repo structure, so you wouldn’t “find them in codebase” at all.\\n\\nRight now, based on evidence, **#2 or #1 looks more likely than “hidden folder in codebase.”**\",\"textSignature\":\"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0a05b6c3657906520169e70cdb09f0819189c2fc674bddf9f4\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}],\"api\":\"openai-codex-responses\",\"provider\":\"openai-codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4\",\"usage\":{\"input\":2686,\"output\":533,\"cacheRead\":12288,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":15507,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.0067150000000000005,\"output\":0.007995,\"cacheRead\":0.003072,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0.017782}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1776749783095}}\n21:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"f4c25df2\",\"parentId\":\"0e98d48a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-21T05:42:07.518Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"message_id\\\": \\\"799\\\",\\n  \\\"reply_to_id\\\": \\\"798\\\",\\n  \\\"sender_id\\\": \\\"1154988359\\\",\\n  \\\"conversation_label\\\": \\\"Fina