{"type":"message","id":"2c11a5af","parentId":"92bbdb6a","timestamp":"2026-04-21T10:59:35.538Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:-5153807254\",\n  \"message_id\": \"824\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"813\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1154988359\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Final Play id:-5153807254\",\n  \"sender\": \"Dev\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-04-21 10:59 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Final Play\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true,\n  \"history_count\": 7\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Dev (1154988359)\",\n  \"id\": \"1154988359\",\n  \"name\": \"Dev\",\n  \"username\": \"Oxpranav\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"emily_bot\",\n  \"body\": \"you’re right, boss.\\n\\nI overstated it earlier, and the screenshot timing backs you up:\\n\\n• the two wolf-research-* sessions shown there were created only after you told me to create them\\n• so the earlier “two subagents” were not existing session objects you could inspect\\n• and they were never in the codebase either\\n\\nSo the clean truth is:\\n\\n• before you explicitly told me to create them: they were just an intended delegation / claimed worker concept, not visible session records\\n• after you told me to create them: they became real session entries in OpenClaw\\n• in the repo/codebase: never, unless I write files for them\\n\\nSo yes, your phrasing is fair:\\n\\n• they were in my head, not in sessions, and not in the codebase\\n\\nI’m glad you pushed on it, because that distinction matters.\"\n}\n```\n\nChat history since last reply (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Thewolf (@Thatiswolf) id:1305029724\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1776764242000,\n    \"body\": \"@pranav iske muh me dede baat ni mann rahi bc\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Dev (@Oxpranav) id:1154988359\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1776764782000,\n    \"body\": \"Arre isne kal setup hi nhi karre the\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Thewolf (@Thatiswolf) id:1305029724\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1776764794000,\n    \"body\": \"ohhh\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Dev (@Oxpranav) id:1154988359\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1776764795000,\n    \"body\": \"Sub agents abhi subah unko sessions mien kara hai\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Dev (@Oxpranav) id:1154988359\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1776764819000,\n    \"body\": \"Abhi Mai todha sa kaam kar raha tha office ka woh karke isko karta hu\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Dev (@Oxpranav) id:1154988359\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1776764837000,\n    \"body\": \"Tu chill karle todhi der mai isko sahi karta hu shaam se pehle pura\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Thewolf (@Thatiswolf) id:1305029724\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1776764993000,\n    \"body\": \"Okie\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\nYou are the main orchestrator agent.\n\nGoal:\nSet up 2 independent subagents, each in its own git worktree, with isolated environments, but with a shared communication pipeline to the main agent.\n\nTasks:\n\n1. Create Worktrees\n- Create two git worktrees from the current repo:\n - /agents/subagent-1\n - /agents/subagent-2\n- Each should be on its own branch:\n - subagent-1-branch\n - subagent-2-branch\n\n2. Environment Setup\n- Each subagent must have:\n - Its own config file (config.json)\n - Its own logs directory\n - Its own task queue file\n\n3. Obsidian Setup\n- Initialize an Obsidian vault inside each subagent directory:\n - /agents/subagent-1/vault\n - /agents/subagent-2/vault\n- Create standard notes:\n - goals.md\n - tasks.md\n - memory.md\n\n4. Communication Pipeline\n- Implement a file-based communication system:\n - /pipeline/main_to_subagent_1.json\n - /pipeline/main_to_subagent_2.json\n - /pipeline/subagent_1_to_main.json\n - /pipeline/subagent_2_to_main.json\n\n- Each agent:\n - Reads its incoming file periodically\n - Writes responses to its outgoing file\n\n5. Agent Roles\n- Main agent:\n - Assign tasks\n - Monitor outputs\n - Update subagent memory\n - Act as coordinator\n\n- Subagents:\n - Execute assigned tasks independently\n - Maintain their own state in memory.md\n - Report progress back via pipeline\n\n6. Training Mechanism\n- Main agent should:\n - Evaluate subagent outputs\n - Write feedback into their memory.md\n - Refine future task assignments\n\n7. Execution Loop\n- Ensure all agents run in parallel (async or separate processes)\n- Add a loop for:\n - read → process → write → sleep\n\nConstraints:\n- Subagents must not directly communicate with each other\n- All communication goes through the main agent\n- System should be modular and extensible"}],"timestamp":1776769175533}}
